description: This is the main entry point for a React-based frontend application. It imports React, ReactDOM, a CSS file, and the App component, then renders the App component into the DOM element with id 'root'.

methods.name: ReactDOM.createRoot
methods.description: Creates a React root for rendering the React component tree into a specified DOM node.

methods.name: root.render
methods.description: Renders a React element (here, the <App /> component) into the DOM.
